@NODE "Map editor" "Get a layout!"
@TOC "MAIN"

                        -- Keys used in Map-editor --

SHIFT M: load a map. (made in Map-editor)
SHIFT S: save a map.
SPACE  : switch between map screen and block screen. Select your blocks on the
         block screen.
+/-    : next/previous screen.
b      : copy current screen into buffer
SHIFT B: copy buffer into current screen
CTRL c : quit Map-editor.

That's it really. Ain't nothing to it. Make sure the entrances and exits are
placed properly and ALWAYS make it possible for our H.E.R.O. to clear the
screen.

Please note that walls, lights and rafts are also enemies which you can edit in
@{"Enemy-editor" LINK "Enemy editor"}.

Map-editor wil ALWAYS save screen 0-99. Don't worry if your level has less
screens, it will be taken care of in the @{"Enemy-editor" LINK "Enemy editor"}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Enemy editor" "Get them baddies going"
@TOC "MAIN"

                       -- Keys used in Enemy-editor --

SHIFT M: load a map. (made in @{"Map-editor" LINK "Map editor"})
SHIFT L: load a level. (saved from Enemy-editor)
SHIFT S: save a level. Make sure your current screen is the LAST screen in
         your level. Enemy-editor wil save screen 0 - current screen.
+/-    : next/previous screen.
CTRL c : quit Enemy-editor.
</>    : next/previous enemy. Enemies are limited to 4 per screen. Don't
         worry, this is sufficient for H.E.R.O.. 
c      : clear current enemy from the screen.
1-0,q,e: select enemy
w      : water on/off (for bottom screens)
t      : test the animation. Press t several times for different enemy-speeds.
         Press any other key to stop.

How to define paths for the raft and the octopus:
First, select the raft or octopus. Then click on the left-most postition and
the select the right-most position. That's it!!! Press 't' to check the path.

Now comes the tricky bit. Connecting screens. All screens are made
in a specific order by you. To make sure they connect check exits and
entrances and connect them using the CRSR-keys.	Levels are placed behind each
other and here's how to connect them.

Say you had an entrance at the north side and your exit is at the west side.
OK? Check out the compass at the bottom of the screen and use the CRSR-keys to
make N -1 and W 1. Why? Well, if you moved North again (Up) you would go back
1 screen in the chain of screens. If you move West you'll move forward 1
screen in our chain. In the next screen East should be -1 and the exit's value
should be 1.

Geddit??? No? Then read it again. It's real simple. Or load up the example
level provided... Ofcourse the first screen doesn't have an entrance and the
last screen doesn't have an exit!! Just make sure the trapped miner is in the
final screen (It would be very annoying for our H.E.R.O. not to have anyone to
resque!!!) :)
@ENDNODE

